!! ## The parts-of-speech are:
+Ex/A
+Ex/Adv
+Ex/N
+Ex/Num
+Ex/V

 +A 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ adjective
 +Adp 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ adposition
 +Adv 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ adverb
 +CS 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ subordinating conjunction
 +CC 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ coordinating conjunction
 +Det  	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ determiner
 +Descr  !!вЙИ * @CODE@ descriptive
 +Interj !!вЙИ * @CODE@ interjection
 +N 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ noun
 +Num 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ numerals
 +Pcle 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ particle
 +Po 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ postposition
 +Pr 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ preposition (in Russian loans)
 +Pron 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ pronoun
 +Qnt 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ quantifier
 +V 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ verb

!! ## Parts of speech are further split up into:
!! Adjectives
 +Adn	!!вЙИ * @CODE@ Adnominal (modifier) !! This is not an NP head like +Pron
 +Bahuvrihi !!вЙИ * @CODE@ This is a nominative-case NP used as an adjective
 +bahuvrihi !!вЙИ * @CODE@ get rid of these for upper-case

!! Adverbs
 +Ideoph !!вЙИ * @CODE@ These are ideophonic descriptors used to modify the verb
             !!  –≤—Л—А–Ї –ї–Є–≤—В—П—Б—М "**flit** and it flew off"
	     !! "Ideophone: A vivid representation of an idea in sound. A word, often
	     !! onomatopoeic, which describes a predicate, qualificative or adverb in 
	     !! respect to manner, colour, sound, smell, action, state or intensity."
	     !! (Doke 1935:118)
 +Manner     !!вЙИ * @CODE@ with reference to type of adverb
 +Parenthetic !!вЙИ * @CODE@ parenthetic
 +Spat 	     !!вЙИ * @CODE@ spatial
 +Iter      !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Iterative  form expressing number of times; myv: `–Ї–∞–≤–Ї—Б—В—М`, kpv: `–Ї—Л–Ї—Л—Б—М`
 +Mult      !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Multiplicative, two-ply; myv: `–Ї–∞–≤–Њ–љ—М–Ї–Є—А–і–∞`
 +Deg 	     !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Ad-adjective This is degree, depricate + AdA
 +Epist	!!вЙИ * @CODE@ epistemic modality marker speaker's evaluation/judgment of, degree of confidence in
 +EvidNfh   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ not first-hand –Ї–µ–ї—П
 +EvidFh    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ first-hand
 +PerifMod  !!вЙИ * @CODE@ periferal modifier —Б—М–Ї–∞–Љ–Њ–љ–Ј–Њ

!! Interjections
 +Formulaic !!вЙИ * @CODE@ 

!! Nouns
 +Prop	!!вЙИ * @CODE@ proper

!! Particles

!! Postpositions
!! **+ Spat**, **+ Temp**

!! ## Pronouns
 +Dem	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ demonstrative
 +Indef  !!вЙИ * @CODE@ indefinite
 +Dep 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ dependent word requiring the presence of another, e.g. **–Љ–µ–љ—М**
 +Exclusive	!!вЙИ * **@CODE@**:  —Б—М–Ї–∞–Љ–Њ–љ–Ј–∞
 +Intensive !!вЙИ * **@CODE@**:  intensive pronoun
 +Interr !!вЙИ * @CODE@ interrogative
 +PerifMod      !!вЙИ * **@CODE@**:  periferal modifier —Б—М–Ї–∞–Љ–Њ–љ–Ј–∞, –Ї–∞–≤–Њ–љ–µ—Б—В
 +Pers 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ personal
 +Recipr !!вЙИ * @CODE@ reciprocal
 +Refl 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ reflexive
 +Rel 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ relative
 +Relat 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ relator noun
 +Sel 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ selective, when selecting from a set of definites
 +Short	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ —В–µ–љ—М, —В–µ—В—М; —Н—Б—В–µ–љ—М
 +Long	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ –Љ–Њ–љ–µ–љ—М, —В–Њ–љ–µ—В—М; –Љ–Њ–љ—Б—В–µ–љ—М

 +Sg1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ first person singular
 +Sg2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ second person singular
 +Sg3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ third person singular
 +Pl1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ first person plural
 +Pl2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ second person plural
 +Pl3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ third person plural


!! ## Quantifiers (numerals)
!! Quantifiers and Numerals are classified under:
 +Appr      !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Approximative numeral –Ї–∞–≤—В–Њ-–Ї–Њ–ї–Љ–Њ, –Ї–Њ–ї–Љ–Њ—И–Ї–∞ *two or three*
            !!          NB! do not confuse with Komi case +Apr
 +AssocColl !!вЙИ * @CODE@ -ne- ; avide-
 +Assoc     !!вЙИ * @CODE@ +–Љ–µ–Ј—В—М
 +Card      !!вЙИ * @CODE@ cardinal + NCard
 +Coll      !!вЙИ * @CODE@ collective
 +Distr     !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Distributive
 +Ord       !!вЙИ * @CODE@ ordinal + NOrd
 +Exclusive     !!вЙИ * **@CODE@**:  —Б—М–Ї–∞–Љ–Њ–љ–Ј–Њ

!! ## Nominals are inflected for Number and Case
!! ## Number
 +Sg !!вЙИ * @CODE@ singular
 +Pl !!вЙИ * @CODE@ plural
 +SP !!вЙИ * @CODE@ ambiguous for number, general number

!! ## Case
 +Abe !!вЙИ * @CODE@ abessive
 +Abl !!вЙИ * @CODE@ ablative case
 +Com !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Comitative "-–љ–µ–Ї/-–љ—Н–Ї"
 +Cmpr !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Comparative case form -—И–Ї–∞
 +Dat !!вЙИ * @CODE@ dative
 +Ela !!вЙИ * @CODE@ elative case
 +Gen !!вЙИ * @CODE@ genitive case
 +Ill !!вЙИ * @CODE@ illative
 +Ine !!вЙИ * @CODE@ inessive
 +Lat !!вЙИ * @CODE@ lative
 +Loc !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Locative "–≤–Є—В—М —С–љ : –≤–Є—В—М —С–љ–Њ"
 +Nom !!вЙИ * @CODE@ nominative case
 +Prl !!вЙИ * @CODE@ prolative "–≥–∞/–Ї–∞/–≤–∞"
 +Tra !!вЙИ * @CODE@ translative: used in similative and depictive constructions
   !! to mark what would be a secondary subject: 
   !! --–≤–∞—А–Љ–∞–Ї—Б –Њ—А–≥–Њ–і—Б—М —В–Њ—Б—В–Њ--
 +Temp !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Temporalis case form "-–љ–µ/-–љ—Н" previously TempCx
 +Voc !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Vocative

!! ## Possession and other declension types are marked with:
 +PxSg1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ first person singular
 +PxSg2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ second person singular
 +PxSg3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ third person singular
 +PxSP3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ third person singular or plural with dative only
 +PxPl1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ first person plural
 +PxPl2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ second person plural
 +PxPl3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ third person plural
 +Def 	!!вЙИ * @CODE@ Definite
!+InDef moved to +Indef ! Indefinite

!! ## The comparative forms are:
 +Comp   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ comparative as opposed to superlative
 +Superl !!вЙИ * @CODE@ superlative
 +Attr 	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Attribute

!! ## Verb moods are:
 +Cond  !!вЙИ * @CODE@ conditional –Ђ–љ–і–µ—А—П- (Derivational)
 +Conj  !!вЙИ * @CODE@ conjunctional "–≤–Ю–ї—М"
 +Des   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ desiderative –Ђ–Ї—Б—Н–ї—М "was about to; wanted to"
 +Ind   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ indicative
 +Imprt !!вЙИ * @CODE@ imperative
 +Opt   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ optative
 +Prec   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ precative
 +Proh	!!вЙИ * @CODE@ prohibitive is distinct from the negation of imperative
 !! –Ш–ї—П –∞–≤–∞—А–і–µ! `Don't cry' (Proh);
 !! –Р–≤–Њ–ї—М –Љ–µ–ї—П–≤—В—В, –Ї–µ—Ж—П–Ї! `Don't worry, be happy!' (Neg + Imprt)

!! ### Infinitive moods
 +Oblig !!вЙИ * @CODE@ modality: deontic/directive/obligative
           !!  –∞–љ–і–Њ–Љ—Б: –∞–љ–і–Њ–Љ–∞ , —П–Ї–∞–Љ—Б: —П–Ї–∞–Љ–∞
 +Delib !!вЙИ * @CODE@ **+Sugg modality**: deontic/directive/deliberative
       !! I still need the right word for this –∞–љ–і–Њ–Љ—Б: –∞–љ–і–Њ–Љ—Б–∞—В

!! ## Tenses in the indicative and infrequently in the conditional
 +Prs !!вЙИ * @CODE@ In Erzya There is no morphological distinction
          !! between present and future
 +Prt1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Preterite 1
 +Prt2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ Preterite 2 (This is also used in predicate forms not involving a finite verb.)

!! ## Verb personal forms are:
! Subject conjugation
 +ScSg1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * subject conjugation first person singular
 +ScSg2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * subject conjugation second person singular
 +ScSg3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * subject conjugation third person singular
 +ScPl1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * subject conjugation first person plural
 +ScPl2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * subject conjugation second person plural
 +ScPl3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * subject conjugation third person plural
!! ## Object conjugation
 +OcSg1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * object conjugation first person singular
 +OcSg2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * object conjugation second person singular
 +OcSg3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * object conjugation third person singular
 +OcPl1 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * object conjugation first person plural
 +OcPl2 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * object conjugation second person plural
 +OcPl3 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * object conjugation third person plural

!! Other verb forms are
 +Act	 !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * active voice (exo-tradition)
 +PrsPrc !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * present participle (only non-contrastive usage)
 +DemPrc !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * present participle (both contrastive and non-contrastive)
  +ActPrcLong  !!вЙИ * @CODE@  {–Є—Л}–є (This is dealt with elsewhere as an active present participle)
  +ActPrcShort !!вЙИ * @CODE@  {–Є—Л}  (This is dealt with elsewhere as an active present participle)
  +ActDemPrc   !!вЙИ * @CODE@  {–Є—Л}—Ж—П  (This is dealt with elsewhere as an active present participle)
  +ConNeg !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * connegative, main verb complement to Neg, vow-stem
  +ConNegII !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * connegative, main verb complement to Neg, cons-stem
  +Ger !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * gerund This is used with Der/Ozj and VAbl
  +Inf    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * infinitive
  +Neg    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * verb of negation —Н–Ј—М, –∞–≤–Њ–ї—М, –Є–ї—П, –∞–њ–∞–Ї
  +ConvPrc !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * converb OR participle –∞–њ–∞–Ї
  +Prc !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * participle
  +VGen   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * Verb Genitive, genitive form participle
  +VAbl   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * Verb Ablative "–Њ–Ј–∞–і–Њ"
  +Prc/Telic !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * Telic participle  "—Б–∞–µ–≤—В—М"
  +Der/Abe   !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * –Т—В–Ю–Љ–Ю
  +Der/Cmpr  !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * —И–Ї–∞
  +Der/A    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * adjective derived from N or V
  +Der/N2A    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * adjective derived from N
  +Der/V2A    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * adjective derived from V
 +Subst	    !!вЙИ * @CODE@ * deverbal nouns retaining verb arguments/gov

